<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="utf-8"/>
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1"/>
<title>Hollywoodbets — Registration Attribution Audit</title>
<script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/Chart.js/4.4.1/chart.umd.min.js"></script>
<style>
:root{
  --ink:#0f1419; --panel:#161d26; --panel2:#1c2530; --line:#2a3744;
  --mute:#7d8b9a; --soft:#aab7c4; --text:#e6edf3;
  --signal:#ffb02e;        /* migration anomaly accent */
  --signal-dim:#7a5410;
  --good:#3fb27f; --bad:#e5544b; --info:#5aa9e6;
  --mono:'SFMono-Regular',ui-monospace,'Cascadia Code','Roboto Mono',Consolas,monospace;
  --sans:'Inter','Segoe UI',system-ui,-apple-system,sans-serif;
}
*{box-sizing:border-box}
html{scroll-behavior:smooth}
body{margin:0;background:var(--ink);color:var(--text);font-family:var(--sans);
  line-height:1.55;-webkit-font-smoothing:antialiased;font-size:15px}
@media(prefers-reduced-motion:reduce){*{animation:none!important;transition:none!important}}

.wrap{max-width:1120px;margin:0 auto;padding:0 24px}
a{color:var(--info);text-decoration:none}
h1,h2,h3{line-height:1.15;margin:0;font-weight:650}
.mono{font-family:var(--mono)}

/* ---- masthead ---- */
.mast{border-bottom:1px solid var(--line);padding:46px 0 38px;
  background:radial-gradient(120% 140% at 80% -10%,rgba(255,176,46,.07),transparent 60%)}
.eyebrow{font-family:var(--mono);font-size:12px;letter-spacing:.22em;text-transform:uppercase;
  color:var(--signal);margin-bottom:18px}
.mast h1{font-size:clamp(28px,4.4vw,46px);letter-spacing:-.02em;max-width:18ch}
.mast .sub{color:var(--soft);margin-top:16px;max-width:64ch;font-size:16px}
.meta{margin-top:22px;display:flex;gap:26px;flex-wrap:wrap;font-family:var(--mono);
  font-size:12.5px;color:var(--mute)}
.meta b{color:var(--soft);font-weight:500}

/* ---- finding banner ---- */
.finding{margin:32px 0 8px;border:1px solid var(--signal-dim);
  background:linear-gradient(180deg,rgba(255,176,46,.08),rgba(255,176,46,.02));
  border-radius:10px;padding:24px 26px;display:flex;gap:18px;align-items:flex-start}
.finding .dot{flex:0 0 auto;width:10px;height:10px;border-radius:50%;background:var(--signal);
  margin-top:8px;box-shadow:0 0 0 4px rgba(255,176,46,.15)}
.finding h2{font-size:18px;color:var(--signal)}
.finding p{margin:8px 0 0;color:var(--soft);max-width:80ch}

/* ---- sections ---- */
section{padding:46px 0;border-bottom:1px solid var(--line)}
.shead{display:flex;align-items:baseline;gap:14px;margin-bottom:8px}
.snum{font-family:var(--mono);font-size:12px;color:var(--signal);letter-spacing:.1em}
.shead h2{font-size:22px;letter-spacing:-.01em}
.sdesc{color:var(--mute);max-width:74ch;margin:0 0 26px;font-size:14.5px}

/* ---- stat cards ---- */
.cards{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(4,1fr);gap:14px}
.card{background:var(--panel);border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:10px;padding:20px}
.card .k{font-family:var(--mono);font-size:11.5px;letter-spacing:.08em;text-transform:uppercase;
  color:var(--mute)}
.card .v{font-family:var(--mono);font-size:30px;font-weight:600;margin-top:10px;letter-spacing:-.02em}
.card .d{font-size:12.5px;color:var(--soft);margin-top:6px}
.card.alert{border-color:var(--signal-dim)} .card.alert .v{color:var(--signal)}
.card.bad .v{color:var(--bad)} .card.good .v{color:var(--good)}

/* ---- chart panel ---- */
.panel{background:var(--panel);border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:10px;padding:22px 22px 16px}
.panel + .panel{margin-top:16px}
.panel h3{font-size:14px;color:var(--soft);margin-bottom:4px}
.panel .ph{font-size:12.5px;color:var(--mute);margin:0 0 18px}
.chart-box{position:relative;height:320px}
.two{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1.35fr 1fr;gap:16px}

/* ---- tables ---- */
.tbl-controls{display:flex;gap:12px;flex-wrap:wrap;align-items:center;margin-bottom:14px}
input.search{background:var(--panel2);border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:8px;color:var(--text);
  padding:10px 14px;font-family:var(--mono);font-size:13px;min-width:260px;flex:1}
input.search:focus{outline:2px solid var(--signal);outline-offset:1px}
.pill{font-family:var(--mono);font-size:12px;color:var(--mute);border:1px solid var(--line);
  border-radius:999px;padding:7px 13px;cursor:pointer;background:var(--panel)}
.pill[aria-pressed=true]{color:var(--ink);background:var(--signal);border-color:var(--signal);font-weight:600}
.tbl-scroll{max-height:560px;overflow:auto;border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:10px}
table{width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;font-size:13px}
thead th{position:sticky;top:0;background:var(--panel2);text-align:left;padding:12px 14px;
  font-family:var(--mono);font-size:11.5px;letter-spacing:.06em;text-transform:uppercase;
  color:var(--mute);border-bottom:1px solid var(--line);cursor:pointer;white-space:nowrap}
thead th:hover{color:var(--soft)}
tbody td{padding:11px 14px;border-bottom:1px solid rgba(42,55,68,.55);vertical-align:top}
tbody tr:hover{background:rgba(255,176,46,.04)}
td.mono{font-family:var(--mono)}
.tag{display:inline-block;font-family:var(--mono);font-size:11px;padding:2px 7px;border-radius:5px;
  background:var(--panel2);border:1px solid var(--line);color:var(--soft);margin:1px 3px 1px 0}
.tag.rsa{background:rgba(255,176,46,.12);border-color:var(--signal-dim);color:var(--signal)}
.tag.gen{color:var(--mute)}
.rowcount{font-family:var(--mono);font-size:12px;color:var(--mute)}
.warn-date{color:var(--signal)}

/* ---- attribution list ---- */
.attr-list{max-height:340px;overflow:auto;padding-right:6px}
.attr-row{display:flex;align-items:center;gap:12px;padding:7px 0;border-bottom:1px solid rgba(42,55,68,.5)}
.attr-row .nm{font-family:var(--mono);font-size:13px;width:120px;flex:0 0 auto}
.attr-row .bar{flex:1;height:8px;background:var(--panel2);border-radius:4px;overflow:hidden}
.attr-row .bar i{display:block;height:100%;background:var(--info)}
.attr-row.gen .bar i{background:var(--mute)}
.attr-row.unk .bar i{background:var(--bad)}
.attr-row .ct{font-family:var(--mono);font-size:12.5px;width:54px;text-align:right;color:var(--soft);flex:0 0 auto}

.note{color:var(--mute);font-size:13.5px;max-width:80ch}
.note code{font-family:var(--mono);background:var(--panel2);padding:1px 6px;border-radius:5px;color:var(--soft)}
ul.clean{margin:14px 0 0;padding-left:18px;color:var(--soft)} ul.clean li{margin:7px 0}
footer{padding:40px 0 60px;color:var(--mute);font-size:12.5px;font-family:var(--mono)}

@media(max-width:860px){
  .cards{grid-template-columns:repeat(2,1fr)} .two{grid-template-columns:1fr}
}
</style>
</head>
<body>

<header class="mast">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="eyebrow">PerformixMedia · Affiliate Data Integrity Audit</div>
    <h1>Hollywoodbets registration attribution: the missing source problem</h1>
    <p class="sub">An 11-month forensic review of player-level reporting (Jul 2025 – May 2026) examining
       players reported with no source ("N/A"), where they actually registered, and a systemic
       duplicate-registration anomaly introduced in May 2026.</p>
    <div class="meta" id="meta"></div>
  </div>
</header>

<div class="wrap">

  <div class="finding">
    <span class="dot"></span>
    <div>
      <h2>Headline finding</h2>
      <p id="finding-text"></p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- 01 SUMMARY -->
  <section id="summary">
    <div class="shead"><span class="snum">01</span><h2>At a glance</h2></div>
    <p class="sdesc">Totals across all eleven monthly exports, de-duplicated to distinct players by core ID
      (the <code style="font-family:var(--mono)">RSA_</code> prefix stripped where present).</p>
    <div class="cards" id="cards"></div>
  </section>

  <!-- 02 ANOMALY -->
  <section id="anomaly">
    <div class="shead"><span class="snum">02</span><h2>What changed in May 2026</h2></div>
    <p class="sdesc">The May export introduced a second copy of existing players under a new
      <code style="font-family:var(--mono)">RSA_</code> ID format. Every one of these copies was stamped with a single
      registration date and carried no source attribution and no financial value — the signature of a
      platform-migration artifact, not real new signups.</p>
    <div class="two">
      <div class="panel">
        <h3>Distinct players vs. unattributed (N/A) players by month</h3>
        <p class="ph">The May bar is split: real attributed players vs. the phantom N/A copies.</p>
        <div class="chart-box"><canvas id="monthChart"></canvas></div>
      </div>
      <div class="panel">
        <h3>Anatomy of the artifact</h3>
        <ul class="clean" id="anatomy"></ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 03 BACK ATTRIBUTION -->
  <section id="attribution">
    <div class="shead"><span class="snum">03</span><h2>Where the N/A players actually registered</h2></div>
    <p class="sdesc">Each N/A player's core ID was matched against its own history in earlier reports to
      recover the original source. The result: the vast majority are not new — they trace back to a known
      sub-ID or to the Generic bucket.</p>
    <div class="two">
      <div class="panel">
        <h3>Recovered source for the 14,008 N/A players</h3>
        <p class="ph">Named sub-IDs are recoverable attribution; "Generic" was already unattributed at source; "Unknown" had no prior history.</p>
        <div class="chart-box"><canvas id="attrDonut"></canvas></div>
      </div>
      <div class="panel">
        <h3>Top recovered sub-IDs</h3>
        <p class="ph">N/A players traced back to a specific named source.</p>
        <div class="attr-list" id="attrList"></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 04 DUPLICATES -->
  <section id="duplicates">
    <div class="shead"><span class="snum">04</span><h2>Duplicate players with conflicting registration dates</h2></div>
    <p class="sdesc">These are core player IDs that appear with more than one distinct registration date across
      the reports — overwhelmingly because the May migration re-stamped an existing player's original signup
      date with the migration date. Search any player ID or sub-ID to inspect the conflict.</p>
    <div class="tbl-controls">
      <input class="search" id="dupSearch" placeholder="Search player ID or sub-ID…" />
      <button class="pill" id="fRsa" aria-pressed="false">Only May-migration cases</button>
      <button class="pill" id="fNamed" aria-pressed="false">Only named sub-IDs</button>
      <span class="rowcount" id="dupCount"></span>
    </div>
    <div class="tbl-scroll">
      <table>
        <thead><tr>
          <th data-k="core_id">Player ID (core)</th>
          <th data-k="ndates">Distinct reg. dates</th>
          <th data-k="dates">Dates seen</th>
          <th data-k="periods">Months present</th>
          <th data-k="sources">Source(s)</th>
        </tr></thead>
        <tbody id="dupBody"></tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <p class="note" style="margin-top:14px">Showing the first <span id="dupShown"></span> matching rows.
      Refine the search to narrow the list.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- 05 METHOD -->
  <section id="method" style="border-bottom:none">
    <div class="shead"><span class="snum">05</span><h2>Method &amp; reading notes</h2></div>
    <p class="sdesc">So the findings hold up to scrutiny.</p>
    <ul class="clean">
      <li><b>Source files:</b> 11 monthly <code>affiliate-player-reporting-export</code> CSVs, Jul 2025 through May 2026. Vendor: Hollywoodbets SA. Affiliate: <code>casinopedia</code>.</li>
      <li><b>Player identity:</b> players are counted by <i>core ID</i> — the numeric ID with any <code>RSA_</code> prefix removed — so a player reported in both formats is recognised as one person.</li>
      <li><b>"N/A" definition:</b> a row with no <code>S1</code> sub-ID and no Affiliate Site Name. In practice this is exactly the set of <code>RSA_</code>-prefixed rows.</li>
      <li><b>Back-attribution:</b> for each N/A player, the recovered source is the most frequent non-Generic source seen for that same core ID in any earlier report; Generic is used only when no named source ever existed.</li>
      <li><b>Caveat:</b> the <code>RSA_</code> rows carry zero deposits, stakes, revenue and commission, so they do not double-count money — but they do inflate raw player/row counts and corrupt registration dates if read at face value.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <footer>
    Prepared for internal review · PerformixMedia · figures derived directly from the supplied monthly exports.
  </footer>
</div>

